HEADWORD: lechatelierite
<hw>lechatelierite</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A naturally occurring
colorless glass made of almost pure silica, and found in fulgurites,
which are produced by lightning striking sand.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> quartz glass, vitreous silica, crystal.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leche</ent>⟦br⟧
